Class PolymerEnricherStatisticsWriter<P extends Polymer>

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, EnricherListener<P>, InteractorEnricherListener<P>, PolymerEnricherListener<P>, AliasesChangeListener<P>, AnnotationsChangeListener<P>, ChecksumsChangeListener<P>, IdentifiersChangeListener<P>, InteractorChangeListener<P>, PolymerChangeListener<P>, XrefsChangeListener<P>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ProteinEnricherStatisticsWriter

    public class PolymerEnricherStatisticsWriter<P extends Polymer>
extends InteractorEnricherStatisticsWriter<P>
implements PolymerEnricherListener<P>
    A statistics logger which records changes made by the enricher. Each addition, removal or update is counted and, upon the completion of the enrichment of the object, is logged in either a file of successes or failures depending on the enrichmentStatus.
    Since:
    18/07/13
    Author:
    Gabriel Aldam (galdam@ebi.ac.uk)
